title: What does the aborted Russian mutiny mean for the war in Ukraine?
description: A sudden uprising in Russia was over too fast to have any immediate impact on the war in Ukraine, but it exposed a fragility in Moscow that Kyiv will seek to exploit, experts have said.

title: Greece's conservative prime minister wins re-election
description: Greece's conservative prime minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis has secured another four-year term in power following a landslide victory in the country's parliamentary elections.

title: Airport worker dies after being sucked into plane engine
description: An airport worker in the US has died after being sucked into a plane engine, officials have said.

title: Titan sub investigators 'taking precautions' in case bodies found on sea floor
description: The US Coast Guard has said investigators looking into the Titan submersible implosion are "taking all precautions" in case they find bodies on the sea floor.

title: On streets of Moscow, people seem shaken up by Wagner rebellion
description: For a capital facing such potentially intense political convulsions, Moscow basked in a sun-drenched Sunday calm.

title: EasyJet flight diverted due to 'unruly' behaviour of two passengers
description: An easyJet flight from the UK to Turkey was diverted to Greece after two passengers became drunk, unruly and started shouting at other people on the plane, authorities said.

title: 'One killed' and several injured in Sweden rollercoaster accident
description: One person has reportedly been killed and several injured in a rollercoaster accident in Stockholm.

title: Ukraine should watch exiled rebel mercenary chief very carefully, warns ex-UK army chief
description: Ukraine is in a strong battlefield position against invading Russian forces but the exile of a rebel mercenary leader to neighbouring Belarus poses a fresh potential threat, a former British Army chief has told Sky News.

title: Hope turns to indifference in Ukraine - but some believe mutiny was only act one of Putin's drama
description: For much of yesterday it seemed Ukraine's enemies were about to turn on themselves.

title: Aborted mutiny busts the myth that Putin is infallible
description: As mutinies go, the march by mercenaries on Moscow was anti-climatic, but history will likely remember 24 June as the moment Vladimir Putin's grip on power started to slip.

title: Rebel Wagner troops to be absorbed into Russian military as Prigozhin heads to Belarus
description: Some Wagner Group mercenaries will join the official Russian military after their leader called off their march on Moscow and agreed to relocate to Belarus.

title: Rebellion in Russia: How the revolt led by 'Putin's Chef' unfolded
description: The Wagner Group staged a rebellion in Russia, in what has been the greatest domestic challenge to Vladimir Putin since he took power.
